[ ] complete CalDAV integration ~#019f027c-4524-78d0-ac22-90ac96b7064d
    >[x] add plan_path to config $ SLICE 1 — config key only, nothing reads it yet. default directory all plans are written to as flat <plan_path>/<charter>/<uid>.ics; projects inherit the default unless they override locally. server owns the calendar collection (.Radicale.props); we only write .ics into it. lands in config.schema.json + configuration.md, the core WorkspaceConfig struct, and each tool's config loading. path-threading is SLICE 2 (see export/import action + README Wiring) $+specifications,library #019f027b-fa30-7701-8920-7592cb9fb943
    >[x] add git-ignored config.local.json layer $ personal per-developer override of a committed project config — slots between .clearhead/config.json and env in load_config precedence (global → project → project.local → env → args). landed: load_config adds the local source after project config; clearhead init writes a scoped .clearhead/.gitignore (config.local.json) before its config-exists guard so existing workspaces pick it up on rerun; debug surfaces project_local_config_file + resolved plan_path; configuration.md documents the full ladder (previously omitted both project layers). verified e2e: plan_path resolves project → local → env in order $+specifications,cli #019f12e0-2490-723a-875e-187dae2663b1
    >[x] export/import/archive read ONLY .ics under plan_path $ SLICE 2 — landed & verified. REVISED the recorded design after reading the caller graph: resolve_workspace_layout is left UNTOUCHED (10 callers, only 2 on the plan path — threading it would make 7 config-blind callers pass None and centralize nothing). Instead the override rides a narrow _with_plans family (load_domain_model_with_plans/Workspace::load_with_plans/load_workspace_with_plans/collect_plan_files_with_plans) over a new pub(crate) leaf collect_plan_files_in(plans_root, project_root_charter); plain fns delegate with None so archive/manifest/graph/save-tests/lsp keep default behavior (no boilerplate). load_workspaces applies config.plan_path to the PRIMARY only. CLI contains it in CommandContext::{plan_override,load_model,load_charters,collect_plan_files,plans_root}; every primary-load call site routes through those. read/expand/plan-archive/export/import/add-plan all honor plan_path (proven e2e: default→empty-when-moved→found-via-override, through both env and config.local.json). GAP by design: charter-level archive (core archive_charter moving a whole charter's plans_dir) still uses default — its handling of server-owned .ics belongs with the next action. never read the caldav server's own sidecar json (radicale's) — server-implementation state, not the shared contract. the server owns the files; we own the actions $+cli,library #019f027d-cafc-7a51-839c-04bdcc615afd
    >[ ] only remove ABSENT ics, never touch present ones $ once a plan's ics is generated the server owns the file — overwrite only when the action changed, never delete one that exists. this is what makes the sharing bidirectional without an integration layer $+specifications,library #019f0284-4096-7943-b065-0ddae837ca4d
    >[ ] add scheduled_at_sync / due_at_sync action properties $ the B column — a stored copy of the action's scheduled/due dates that serves as the three-way merge base. domain model + DSL parse/serialize + graph + action_file_format spec $+specifications,library #019f12da-3161-778f-bc2f-5bf7b9dda3f4
    >[ ] implement the three-way reconcile (A/B/C table) $ A=action date, B=sync-copy, C=ics date; compare each to B to decide no-op / write-C+B / write-A+B / remove / conflict per Decision 31's table. land action and sync-copy (A+B) together via the write-durability seam $+library #019f12d4-4f7c-7bc2-9c76-b048067d43e8
    >[ ] conflict-merge for the four conflict rows $ surface the conflict and let the user choose — both-changed: which source wins; change-vs-removal: whether the removal or the edit is intended. never silently pick $+cli,library #019f121e-1690-713d-bc14-ab564ea38179
    >[ ] treat B changed/removed as a BUG $ B is our own merge base and should only move when reconcile moves it. if a run finds B drifted, log loudly and surface guidance rather than treating it as a normal edit $+library #019f12b8-fa9e-7b2f-8875-19a9c17054b4
